 different regions within a single pocket universe) are causally disconnected
 and are seen by observers as separate universes.
 It appears to be impossible to predict with certainty the values of the
 cosmological parameters that we measure at our present position in the
 multiverse.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To overcome these problems, one may change focus and concentrate on obtaining
 the 
\emph on
probability distribution
\emph default
 of values for the measured cosmological observables, such as the cosmological
 constant, coupling constants, or particle masses.
 Heuristically, one would like to compute probability distributions of the
 cosmological parameters as measured by an observer 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

randomly located
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

