 This solves the flatness problem.
 In fact, the amount of inflation in generic models is much larger than
 
\begin_inset Formula $60$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $e$
\end_inset

-foldings, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

