\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 It is more useful to obtain a differential equation with respect to the
 final value 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 This is derived as follows.
 The distribution 
\begin_inset Formula $P(\phi_{1},\phi_{2},t_{1},t_{2})$
\end_inset

