 Now we use the property 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
P(\phi_{1},\phi_{2},t,t)=\delta(\phi_{1}-\phi_{2})
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 in order to eliminate 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{23}$
\end_inset

 in Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:FP 1 equ 3"

\end_inset

), and finally obtain
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\partial_{t_{2}}P_{12}=\hat{L}_{\phi_{2}}^{\dagger}P_{12}.
\end{equation}

\end_inset

This coincides with Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:FP c"

\end_inset

).
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Now we would like to change the integration variable from 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 to 
