\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 and the scale factor 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

.
 This distribution is interpreted as the fraction of the comoving volume
 where the field has the value 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 and the scale factor has the value 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

, within an equal-
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 hypersurface.
 Alternatively, 
\begin_inset Formula $P(\phi,a,t)$
\end_inset

 is the probability of the field having the value 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 and the scale factor having the value 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 along a single, randomly chosen comoving trajectory.
 The distribution 
\begin_inset Formula $P(\phi,a,t)$
\end_inset

 is the solution of the FP equation
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\partial_{t}P=\hat{L}_{\phi}^{\dagger}P-\partial_{a}\left(aHP\right),
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{L}_{\phi}^{\dagger}$
