key "Winitzki:2001np"
literal "true"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
W\left(\phi\right)=6\pi^{2}\left[\int_{\phi_{q}}^{\phi}\frac{d\phi}{H\left(\phi\right)}\right]^{2},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{q}$
\end_inset

 is the boundary of fluctuation-dominated range of 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

.
 This calculation shows that the probability of having eternal points, 
\begin_inset Formula $X(\phi)=1-\bar{X}\left(\phi\right)$
\end_inset

, exponentially rapidly approaches 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 in the fluctuation-dominated regime.
