\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until now, we considered eternal self-reproduction due to random walk of
 a scalar field.
 Another important class of models includes self-reproduction due to bubble
 nucleation.
 Such scenarios of eternal inflation were studied in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Gott:1982zf,Guth:1982pn,Gott:1984ps,Bucher:1994gb,Bucher:1995et,Yamamoto:1995sw"
literal "true"

\end_inset

.
 Both processes (tunneling and random walk) may be combined in a single
 scenario called 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

recycling universe
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Garriga:1997ef"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, but we will consider them separately for clarity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a locally de Sitter universe dominated by dark energy, nucleation of
 bubbles of false vacuum may occur due to tunneling
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Coleman:1977py,Coleman:1980aw,Hawking:1982my,Lee:1987qc"
literal "true"

\end_inset

.
 The bubble nucleation rate 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

 per unit 4-volume is very small
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Coleman:1980aw,Garriga:1993fh"
literal "true"

\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\Gamma=O(1)H^{4}\exp\left[-S_{I}-\frac{\pi}{H^{2}}\right],\label{eq:nucleation rate}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{I}$
\end_inset

 is the instanton action and 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 is the Hubble constant of the parent de Sitter background.
 Hence, bubbles will generically not merge into a single false-vacuum domain
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Guth:1982pn"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, and infinitely many bubbles will be nucleated at different places and
 times.
 The resulting 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

daughter
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 bubbles may again contain an asymptotically de Sitter, infinite universe,
 which again gives rise to infinitely many 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

grand-daughter
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 bubbles.
 This picture of eternal self-reproduction was called the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

recycling universe
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Garriga:1997ef"
literal "true"

\end_inset

.
 Some (or all) of the created bubbles may support a period of additional
 inflation followed by reheating, as illustrated in Fig.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "cap:A-spacetime-diagram-bubble"

\end_inset

.
 We note that the presence of eternal self-reproduction in models of tunneling
 type is generically certain (unless the nucleation rate for terminal vacua
 is unusually high) because every bubble continues expanding for a long
 time before the next nucleation can occur.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the model of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Garriga:1997ef"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, there were only two vacua that could tunnel into each other.
 A more recently developed paradigm of 
\series bold
string theory landscape
\series default

