\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 in a region of type 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 will never reach parts of the reheating surface of different type 
\begin_inset Formula $k\neq j$
\end_inset

.
 Thus the spherical cutoff yields only the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $\chi_{a}$
\end_inset

