 In the volume-based approach, every bubble nucleated anywhere in the spacetime
 needs to be counted; in the worldline-based approach, only bubbles intersected
 by a selected worldline are counted.
 Let us now explain and examine these two prescriptions in more detail.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since the set of all bubbles is infinite, one needs in any case to perform
 a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

regularization,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 that is, one needs to select a very large but 
\emph on
finite
\emph default
 subset of bubbles.
 The weight 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{\alpha}$
\end_inset

