\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Having obtained adequate analytic approximations for 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{*}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $g(z_{*},\phi)$
\end_inset

, we can now proceed to the calculation of the mean volumes 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle \left.\mathcal{V}_{1,2}\right|_{\mathcal{V}}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 of regions reheated through channels 1 and 2 respectively, conditioned
 on the event that the total volume of all reheated regions is 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{V}$
\end_inset

.
 We use the formalism developed in Sec.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:FPRV-distribution-of-Q"

\end_inset

, where the variable 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

 now takes only the discrete values 1 and 2, so instead let us denote that
 value by 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

.
