)–(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:I equ 1 BB"

\end_inset

).
 Let us introduce the generating function 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
g(z,\left\{ q_{i}\right\} ,\left\{ r_{i}\right\} ;j)\equiv\left\langle z^{n_{\text{tot}}}\prod_{i}q_{i}^{n_{i}}r_{i}^{N_{i}}\right\rangle _{n_{\text{tot}}<\infty;j},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the total number of bubbles of type 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the total number of 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

-regions of type 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
 The number of BBs in bubbles of type 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 is proportional to 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{i}$
\end_inset

 with a proportionality constant 
\begin_inset Formula $\kappa_{i}^{BB}$
\end_inset

, which is the (extremely small) nucleation rate of a BB per Hubble 4-volume
 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{i}^{-4}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The generating function 
\begin_inset Formula $g(z,\left\{ q_{i}\right\} ,\left\{ r_{i}\right\} ;j)$
\end_inset

, which we will denote for brevity by 
\begin_inset Formula $g(...,j)$
\end_inset

, satisfies a system of equations analogous to Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:g general equ"

\end_inset

),
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
g^{\frac{1}{\nu}}(...,j)=\sum_{k\neq j}\kappa_{j\rightarrow k}zq_{k}r_{k}g(...,k)+\kappa_{j\rightarrow j}r_{j}g(...,j).\label{eq:g equ with BB}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Let us compute the RV-regulated ratio of the number of 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

-regions of type 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 to the number of bubbles of the same type 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

.
 This ratio is given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\frac{\left\langle N_{j}\right\rangle _{n}}{\left\langle n_{j}\right\rangle _{n}}=\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\left.\frac{\partial_{z}^{n}\partial_{r_{j}}g(...,i')}{\partial_{z}^{n}\partial_{q_{j}}g(...,i')}\right|_{z=0,r_{i}=1,q_{i}=1},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $i'$
\end_inset

