 To evaluate the limit, we use the methods developed in Sec.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Bubble-abundances-landscape"

\end_inset

.
 The derivatives 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial_{q_{j}}g\equiv\left|h_{j}(z)\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, as defined in Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:hjzk def"

\end_inset

), satisfy Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Mh Q"

\end_inset

).
 The vector of derivatives
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left.\frac{\partial}{\partial r_{j}}\right|_{r_{i}=1,q_{i}=1}g(...,k)\equiv\left|\rho_{j}(z)\right\rangle _{k}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

