 transition.
 If some subset of vacua form a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

disconnected island
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 in the landscape, such that transitions to and from the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

island
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 are forbidden, one can regard the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

island
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 as a separate irreducible landscape and apply the same techniques to that
 landscape.
 Hence, it is sufficient to consider only irreducible landscapes; we will
 from now on always assume that the landscape is irreducible.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 a nonnegative matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}$
\end_inset

 has a unique nondegenerate, real eigenvalue 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{0}>0$
\end_inset

 such that all the eigenvalues of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}$
\end_inset

 (which may be complex-valued) are located within the circle 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\lambda\right|\leq\alpha_{0}$
\end_inset

 in the complex 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 plane.
 This 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

dominant
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

