\begin_layout Standard
Nevertheless, the functions 
\begin_inset Formula $g(z;i)$
\end_inset

 are bounded from above.
 To see this, consider the relationship 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left\langle u^{0}\right|\hat{M}=\lambda_{0}\left\langle u^{0}\right|,
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 written in components as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
u_{j}^{0}(z)\left[\frac{1}{\nu}g^{\frac{1}{\nu}-1}(z;j)-\kappa_{j\rightarrow j}\right]-\sum_{i\neq j}u_{i}^{0}(z)z\kappa_{i\rightarrow j}=\lambda_{0}u_{j}^{0}.
