\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{d}{dz}\det\hat{M}(z)=\bigl(\det\hat{M}(z)\bigr)\text{Tr}\bigl(\hat{M}^{-1}\frac{d\hat{M}}{dz}\bigr)<0
\end{equation}

\end_inset

since it was already found that the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{M}^{-1}(z)$
\end_inset

 has all positive elements while 
\begin_inset Formula $d\hat{M}/dz$
\end_inset

 has all nonpositive elements.
