\begin_layout Standard
The results derived so far — the monotonic behavior of 
\begin_inset Formula $g(z;j)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{0}(z)$
\end_inset

, the positivity of the matrix elements of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{M}^{-1}$
\end_inset

, the bounds on 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 — hold for all 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset

 for which 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{0}(z)>0$
\end_inset

.
 Now we will show that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{0}(z)$
\end_inset

 cannot remain positive for all real 
\begin_inset Formula $z>0$
\end_inset

.
 We can rewrite Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:g equ for q1"

\end_inset

) as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
z\sum_{i\neq k}\kappa_{k\rightarrow i}g(z;i)=g^{\frac{1}{\nu}}(z;k)-\kappa_{k\rightarrow k}g(z;k).
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Using the property 
\begin_inset Formula $g(z;j)>0$
\end_inset

 and the bound
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:gz less 1 over nu"

\end_inset

), we obtain (for every 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

) an upper bound on 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset

