\begin_inset Formula $g(z;j)$
\end_inset

 near 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $0<g(z;j)<\infty$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $0<\partial_{z}g(z;j)<\infty$
\end_inset

 for all those 
\begin_inset Formula $z>0$
\end_inset

 for which this solution branch remains real-valued.
