\begin_inset Formula $g(z;j)$
\end_inset

 could then be continued further to some 
\begin_inset Formula $z>z_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore, the real-valued solution branch 
\begin_inset Formula $g(z;j)$
\end_inset

 must exist for all 
\begin_inset Formula $z>0$
\end_inset

.
 This is incompatible with the bound
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:z global bound"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

