\end{equation}

\end_inset

Since we are only interested in the qualitative behavior of 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{0}(z)$
\end_inset

 at 
\begin_inset Formula $z=z_{*}$
\end_inset

, we do not need to keep track of the complicated coefficients in Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:lambda rel 0"

\end_inset

).
 Near 
\begin_inset Formula $z=z_{*}$
\end_inset

 we have, by Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:M inverse"

\end_inset

), 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
